# Debugging in Production

In mine and your life, 3 things are guaranteed: death, taxes, and bugs. This sections deals with how we can resolve bugs in production, fast. 


## Bug Tracking

A bug tracking software captures and organizes errors, as they happen to users, so you fix problems before they cause widespread user abandonment.
![Bug Tracking](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omkarcloud/botasaurus/master/images/debugging-in-production/bug-tracking.png)

Bug Tracking is really great because 
- Most users won’t report bugs—they’ll just abandon your app. Bug tracking helps fix issues you never would have known about otherwise
- It's much time saving to look up an error in Sentry, and resolve it than waiting for a user to tell us how they got the error, then reproducing it, finding the stack trace, and resolving it.

I have saved many hours of my life, due to Bug Tracking. 

I use Sentry, because it's free, and captures errors with full context (stack traces, user actions, environment details), making it easier to fix issues.

