### How to see a JavaScript code of a Installer?

### Windows 
1.  Find the application's shortcut on your Desktop or in the Start Menu.
2.  **Right-click** on the shortcut and select **"Open file location"**.
![Open File Location](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omkarcloud/botasaurus/master/images/debugging-in-production/open-file-location.png)
5. Drag and Drop `resources` folder in VS Code.
6. Run command 
```
npx asar extract app.asar ./source-code
```
7. You can find the source code in `./source-code/dist` folder.
![Extracted Source Code](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omkarcloud/botasaurus/master/images/debugging-in-production/extracted-source-code.png)

### Mac
1. Go to `Applications` folder. 
![Mac Applications Folder](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omkarcloud/botasaurus/master/images/debugging-in-production/mac-applications-folder.png)
2. Show package contents of the app.
![Show Package Contents](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omkarcloud/botasaurus/master/images/debugging-in-production/show-package-contents.png)
3. Navigate to `Contents/`.
5. Drag and Drop `Resources` folder in VS Code.
